                <p class="stack-desc">For low-power devices — door sensors, light bulbs, leak detectors — we use Zigbee, Z-Wave, or Thread. Every Zigbee 3.0 packet is wrapped in <strong style="color:var(--orange);">AES-128-CCM encryption</strong> and signed against a per-network key. Devices form a mesh: each one helps relay messages, so no single point of failure. The Zigbee logo is a bee for a reason — every node in the hive helps every other node.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="flow-down"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor"><path d="M12 4v16m0 0l-6-6m6 6l6-6" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg></div>

